ce:section.ce:para:
The Z-scheme photocatalysts were constructed through two steps (Scheme 1
                           ). Firstly, carbon dots (CDs) and copolymerization jointly modified g-C3N4, I-ABNx-C3N4@CDsy, was prepared by the co-calcination of urea, glucose and I-ABN. Secondly, BiOI was deposited on the surface of I-ABNx-C3N4@CDsy through solvothermal method. In the above two steps, there are three variables, i.e. the added amount of glucose to urea, the added amount of I-ABN to urea, and the mass fraction of BiOI in g-C3N4/BiOI composite. The best component of photocatalysts was determined by an orthogonal experiment. According to the above three variables, the formulas of the orthogonal experiment were designed and summarized in Table 1
                           . For 6 g of urea, the added amount of glucose is 2, 3, and 4 mg; and the added amount of I-ABN is 2.5, 5, and 7.5 mg. Furthermore, the weight contents of BiOI in the composites photocatalysts were 7.5, 10, 12.5 wt%. As shown in Table 1, the resulting photocatalysts with different components were named PC1–PC9.
